==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wilton carpet
<hw>Wil"ton car`pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A kind of carpet woven with
loops like the Brussels, but differing from it in having the loops cut
so as to form an elastic velvet pile; -- so called because made
originally at <ets>Wilton</ets>, England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wilwe</ent>⟦br⟧
